parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt latch can cause the seat belt to come undone while driving, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt latch will not stay latched
the seat belt will not lock into the buckle
the seat belt latch fails to release when the release button is pressed
the seat belt does not lock.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shut-off or stalling of the engine can lead to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine shuts off or stalls without warning
loss of power steering and brakes

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine overheating can cause damage to the engine, coolant system, and other components, leading to costly repairs, breakdowns, and potentially catastrophic failures.

Failure of critical engine components, such as the engine head, can lead to costly repairs, breakdowns, and potentially catastrophic failures.
